  schema:name "Cosmic Distance Ladder" ;
  schema:description "The cosmic distance ladder is the sequence of techniques used to measure distances in the universe, each method calibrating the next: [parallax](./parallax.md) to Cepheid variables to [Type Ia supernovae](./type-ia-supernova.md) to the Hubble flow." ;
